Task 1 :
Create a connection profile for the new network interface on server using a text editing tool. Assign the IP 192.168.0.170/24 with gateway 192.168.0.1 and set it to autoactivate at system reboots.
Deactivate and reactive this interface at the command prompt.


# vim /etc/sysconfig/network-scripts/ifcfg-eth1
## The config file is a KEY=value pair 
TYPE=ethernet 
BOOTPROTO=none
ONBOOT=yes
IPADDR=192.168.0.170
GATEWAY=192.168.0.1
PREFIX=24
DEVICE=eth1


# ifup eth1
# nmcli con sh 
# ip a s 
